main – Fully DFSG‑free software Debian supports directly.  

contrib – Free itself, but depends on non‑free bits.  

non‑free – Redistributable but not fully free (licenses restrict).  

non‑free‑firmware – Moved out in newer releases to make firmware handling clearer (important for Wi‑Fi, GPUs, NICs).



Beyond the main suite categories, Debian provides special update channels: 

security Timely security fixes for stable Always enable in production. 

updates (aka stable‑updates) Urgent fixes that can’t wait for the next point release (e.g., timezone, essential bugfix) Recommended for most installs. 

proposed‑updates Candidate packages for the next point release (staging) Test labs before large fleet upgrades. 

backports Selected packages rebuilt from testing (newer versions) for stable Use sparingly, per‑package installs; good for new kernels, drivers, language runtimes.


/etc/apt/sources.list.d/

# /etc/apt/sources.list 
deb http://deb.debian.org/debian bookworm main contrib non-free non-free-firmware 
deb http://deb.debian.org/debian-security bookworm-security main contrib non-free non-free-firmware 
deb http://deb.debian.org/debian bookworm-updates main contrib non-free non-free-firmware 
# backports are opt-in; comment out until needed: 
# deb http://deb.debian.org/debian bookworm-backports main contrib non-free non-free-firmware




